HEADWORD: Mesprise
<hw>Mes*prise"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>mespris</ets>, F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧pris</ets>. See
<er>Misprize</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Contempt; scorn.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Perh. for F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧prise</ets> mistake. Cf.
<er>Misprision</er>.]</ety> <def>Misadventure; ill-success.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

